      "created_at": "2022-09-07T07:44:47.467Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I use a spin bike with Assioma pedals <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"> I really like the silence of it.  My wife would never let me bring a real bike in the house <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"></p>\n<p>Our logic is that it should definitly prioritize the power meter over the virtual power.  I don\u2019t see any reason to have the spin bike connected.  You get both RPM and power from the pedals.  So simplist is just disconnect the iC4.</p>",
